Ewing Sarcoma Gene Suppression RNA-Seq Analysis

Dec 28, 2022

Ewing sarcoma is a pediatric bone cancer which arises from the fusion of the EWSR1 and FLI1 genes (EWSR1-FLI1 fusion oncogene). Recently, some have proposed therapies for Ewing sarcoma which suppress EWSR1-FLI1. This RNA-Seq analysis compares gene expression in an Ewing sarcoma cell line with and without EWS-FLI knockdown.

Principal Components Plot

Data was first normalised using regularised log transformation (rlog). This was used to plot the first two principal components (PCs). The first PC separates the two conditions. This shows that a lot of the variation in gene expression in the dataset can likely be explained by the differences between experimental conditions and there are no other major sources of variation in the data that need to be accounted for.

MA Plot

To perform differential gene expression analysis, raw counts for each gene were fit to the DESeq negative binomial model. An MA plot was produced to visualise the results. The MA plot shows the average expression of each gene versus the log2 fold change. The points are coloured blue if the adjusted p-value is less than 0.1. Log fold change (LFC) shrinkage was performed using the apeglm method. This method is designed to reduce the bias in log fold change estimates caused by low average expression levels.

Differentially Expressed Genes

Differentially expressed genes were defined as those with an adjusted p-value less than 0.01, a log2 fold change of at least 1, and an average expression level of at least 20 counts. A table of the resulting differentially expressed genes is shown below.

Volcano Plot

A volcano plot was created to look at the distribution of fold changes relative to the adjusted p-value.

Top 20 Differentially Expressed Genes

The heatmap below looks at the top 10 over-expressed genes and the top 10 under-expressed genes based on log2 fold change obtained after LFC shrinkage. rlog normalised counts for each gene were used.

Gene Set Enrichment Analysis

Gene Set Enrichment Analysis (GSEA) was performed to identify enriched gene sets in KEGG pathways. The GSEA metric was calculated as follows: gsea metric = -log10(padj) * sign(log2FoldChange). The results of the GSEA analysis are shown in the table below.
